race.comment: FAST FREEZE (7) is a former Victorian who seeks the hat-trick off easy wins at Kununurra. They stack up and the improved galloper has been freshened. Has an awkward gate to deal with but she can win if she transfers the form. HELL FIRE MISS (9) is busting to win again and comes back in grade off the latest. She's another with an awkward gate but has winning claims. FRAWLEY (2) found one too good seeking the hat-trick at this level but covered the others. Maps well and is also a chance. KISSING SUPIDO (5) has been plainer since the big 66 win over shorter but it's hard to risk the potent Todd-Clarke linkage.
